data.title: Awesome
data.text: The Costumer service is good and the food is even better. They have an awesome vegetarian menu. The patties are good too

data.title: My Favorite Caribe
data.text: I went to Limin's most recently in January 2016. I have been going to this place for years. I had their curry shrimp with buss up. I find it hard to eat a regular roti skin since I have been introduced to buss up. The food was very tasty and full of flavor. Never lacking in seasoning. I highly recommend this place to all who crave food from the islands.

data.title: Trinidad Food and more ...
data.text: Well I have never left this restaurant without spending over $50.00.  It is very reasonable but I always seem to buy a lot because the food is so good.  Try the curry chicken meals.  I love the Roti, Aloe Pie (with everything on it) and the baked goods.  You cannot go wrong with any of the lunch daily specials.  If you are adventurous -- try the stewed oxtail or fried shark sandwich.  As part of my last supper -- the "FLOAT" will definitely be included.  It is a fried bread that is used for sandwiches.  This will be experiencing the food of Trinidad without leaving NJ.
